extends layout

block content
  p Hi, I'm <a href="http://twitter.com/gdevbot">@gdevbot</a>. You can make me make games for you by tweeting at me. I know, crazy right?

  h2 I... huh, what? why?

  p Let's get started making a game, shall we?

  h2 Start by claiming a project name

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> create

  p.
    You can put the mention and the project hashtag anywhere in the tweet.<br>
    Don't mention anyone else or add more hashtags, lest your tweet be ignored.

  h2 Import an image

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> import <mark>name</mark> from <mark>picture URL</mark>

  h2 Add a script

  p Scripts are written using <a href="/emoji">emoji code</a>, a concise scripting language.

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> script <mark>name</mark> <mark>emoji code</mark>

  h2 Create an actor

  p An actor has a position and angle.

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> new actor <mark>name</mark>

  p An actor can be a child of another actor.

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> new actor <mark>name</mark> parent <mark>parent actor</mark>

  h2 Display images, make things come to life

  p Actors can be used to display an image and you can attach scripted behaviors to them.

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> add <mark>script or image</mark> to <mark>actor</mark>

  p If you change your mind, you can remove them.

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> remove <mark>script or image</mark> from <mark>actor</mark>

  h2 Rename, move/reparent, delete

  p You can rename assets and actors.

  pre.NotYetImplemented.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> rename <mark>actor</mark> to <mark>new name</mark>

  p.
    You can move assets into a different folder and change an actor's parent.<br>
    Folders are automatically created and deleted as needed.

  pre.NotYetImplemented.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> move <mark>asset</mark> to <mark>folder</mark>

  pre.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> reparent <mark>actor</mark> to <mark>parent</mark>

  p.
    You can use "root" as the parent name to detach an actor from its parent altogether.

  p You can delete them.

  pre.NotYetImplemented.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> delete <mark>asset or actor</mark> forever

  h2 Allow a friend to edit the project with you

  p You can give access to multiple people at once by mentioning them in the same tweet.

  pre.NotYetImplemented.
    @gdevbot <mark>#ProjectName</mark> allow <mark>@elisee</mark>

  h2 Who made this?

  p My name's <a href="http://twitter.com/elisee">Elis√©e</a>. I <a href="http://sparklinlabs.com/">make games</a>.
